<paragraph blockId="3.[388,1562,805,2172]" pageId="3" pageNumber="251">
The teeth are rather stnaller than those of 
<taxonomicName box="[1172,1523,805,838]" class="Reptilia" family="Hadrosauridae" genus="Hadrosaurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="3" pageNumber="251" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="foulkei">
<emphasis box="[1172,1523,805,838]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="251">Hadrosaurus foulkei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The borders present no indication of the 
<emphasis box="[1148,1300,853,886]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="251">crenation</emphasis>
seen in that and other 
<emphasis box="[568,681,902,935]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="251">species</emphasis>
, either in worn or unworn specimens.
</paragraph>
